Cryptographic implementation note
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The secp256k1 ECDSA signer in `aether_protocol_c/ephemeral_signer.py` is an
original, pure-Python implementation written for auditability. It uses the
same curve parameters as the secp256k1 standard (also used by Bitcoin) and
RFC 6979 deterministic-k nonce generation. It depends on no third-party
cryptography library.

This software is provided for engineering and research use. See SECURITY.md
for the threat model and the precise meaning of "quantum-safe" in this
project (a temporal-safety argument, not post-quantum cryptography).
